## Mini React Assignment: Interactive Dashboard with Public APIs

```Build a React app that fetches data from a public API and includes dynamic interactions like filtering, selection, state sharing, and messaging between components.```

#### 1. Pages / Views

	- Home Page
	- Item Detail Page
	- Dashboard / Stats Page
	- About / Info Page

#### 2. Dynamic Interaction Components

	- Search/Filter Component
	- Favorites Component
	- Comment Box
	- Interactive Chart

#### 3. State Management & Communication

    - Component-level state: For search input, comment input, toggle buttons
    - Shared state: Favorites, selected item stats
    - Props drilling or Context API: For communication between Header, Home, and Favorites components

#### 4. Suggested Public APIs

    - PokéAPI (https://pokeapi.co/api/v2/pokemon) → Pokémon list, types
    - JSONPlaceholder (https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts) → Posts, users, comments
    - OMDb API → Movies, ratings, genres
    - CoinGecko API → Coins, prices, categories
    - Rapid API → https://rapidapi.com/collections

#### 5. Features

    - Data fetching with fetch or axios
    - Loading & error handling states
    - Routing with React Router
    - Favorites/bookmarks with shared state
    - Dynamic charts & statistics
    - Interactive comment section

#### 6. Bonus

    - Persist favorites and comments in localStorage
    - Add a notification toast when user adds/removes favorites or comments
    - Add pagination or infinite scroll for large data sets
    - Add drag-and-drop reordering of favorite items (React DnD)

#### 7. Deliverables

    - React project in GitHub
    - Functional pages with  dynamic data (using useEffect)
    - Interactive stateful components (favorites, search, comments)
    - Dashboard with dynamic stats or charts
    - README explaining


